[Info] The run has now ended! We've switched over to Pokémon Stadium 2 for the intermission; our next run will be Pokémon Colosseum, beginning Monday, April 15th at 21:00 UTC. See you there!

[Recap] While exploring Ultra Space, the Ultra Moon side has found a lot more rare Pokémon, namely capturing Pheromoasa, Cobalion, Celesteela, Mesprit, Regice, Regirock, Xurxitree, Lugia, Regigigas, Zekrom, Articuno, Moltres, Yveltal, Latias, Kyogre, Mewtwo, Cresselia, Entei, Virizion, Terrakion, and Uxie.

[Recap] The Ultra Moon side entered the Hall of Fame once more since the last update, by defeating Pokémon Trainer Hau around 7d 20h 35m using a team made up of Krookodile (Redemption), Sandslash (Coldsteel), Naganadel (OU), Lunala (Nebby), Zweilous (Zweilous), and Decidueye (Emiya)!

[Recap] Since the last update, the Ultra Moon side collected all 100 Totem Stickers, while the Sun side completed the Alola Pokédex and defeated Battle Legend Red in the Battle Tree.
